Beneath the canopy' endless azure sky, where whispers do not betray,  
The whispering leaves converse in hushed tones on high;   
A symphony that paints its colors bold and bright - it sighs with grace upon my face.    
Nature’s canvas breathes life into the heart of mine eyes so wide, where dreams hold no bounds or trace.  
Forests deep green embrace me in their arms as I roam through verdant lace;   
The skyline kissed by sunbeams play and cast a golden gleaming grace upon her face.    
Cascading waterfalls whisper tales of ancient love, where time is but an echo from afar -  
A lullaby in every drop that falls with gentle touch on earthen floor beneath the trees so tall;   
Infinite oceans hum tunes as they lazily roll and round.    
Beneath my feet I find their rhythm, crisp leaves rustle stories untold of times when nature reigned supreme -  
And for a moment in time, all is known to me without fear or dread;   
A harmony profound where life’s essence unfolds and ends.    
Here the beauty resides that I seek with every breath astounds my soul divine – so pure!
